items.title: SYou’ll Never Guess What Parents Are Still Naming Their Babies - Six Years in a Row
items.description: In news that feels more like déjà vu than data, the Social Security Administration dropped its annual baby name rankings—and let’s just say originality isn’t trending. For the sixth year running, the same two names are holding the crown, while the rest of the list could double as the guest registry at an artisanal juice bar in Portland. Experts are calling it a shift toward “cross-cultural appeal,” but we’re starting to suspect parents are just crowdsourcing names from TikTok and travel blogs. Don’t believe me? There’s only one way to find out.
